metadata.name: Euphonic #604
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moir√© effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

metadata.name: Uncrossed Paths #11
metadata.description:
Many agents start at random locations in random directions (up, down, left or right). There is a small chance that they might turn at any frame. Also, there is a small chance of a new agent being born perpendicular to any agent.
The ultimate rule is, the paths must not be crossed. If an agent comes across its own or another agent‚Äôs path, it turns and moves on. If there is no way to go, the agent stops.
The maximum animation time is 22 sec, although most of the token gets completed around 15 sec.
These simple rules, paired with some chosen palettes can generate beautiful figures.

Press r - restart the animation with different settings (primary traits stay the same)
Press s - save 2048x2048 png in live mode

metadata.name: Fracture #70
metadata.description:
Fragments of fragments, pieced together.


Please be patient as previews may take a while to generate.
Press 's' in live view to save the current image.
You can modify the URL to specify an image size. Keep in mind that the color palette, styles, and general look of the piece will generally remain the same, but a new image will be created to fit the new dimensions. To do this, add x and y URL parameters to the end of the URL. (Images are created using a pixel ratio of 2, so adding ?x=2560&y1440 to the end of the URL will actually create a 5120x2880 image.)
